      "content": "okay but if UNCLOS is the \"dominant standard,\" does that basically mean china's claims are just illegitimate? it feels like you're saying the western view is the only one that matters legally. what about the argument that UNCLOS is just a tool being used by the west to undermine other nations sovereignty?",
